sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant KFP as KFP API Server
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows
    participant Init as odh-pipelines-components<br/>(Init Container)
    participant DL as dataset_download<br/>Component
    participant Train as train_model<br/>Component (LoRA/OSFT/SFT)
    participant Eval as universal_llm_evaluator<br/>Component
    participant Deploy as kubeflow_model_registry<br/>Component
    participant S3 as AWS S3<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrainerPods as Training Worker Pods<br/>(GPU)
    participant PVC as PVC Workspace<br/>(Filesystem)
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM<br/>(Local Inference)

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Init,KFP: Flow 1: Managed Pipeline Staging (Platform Startup)
        Init->>Init: generate_managed_pipelines.py<br/>Compiles pipeline.py → YAML
        Init->>KFP: Copy YAMLs to /config/managed-pipelines<br/>(shared volume mount)
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 2: Fine-Tuning Pipeline (LoRA/OSFT/SFT)
        User->>KFP: Submit fine-tuning pipeline run
        KFP->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow

        Argo->>DL: Step 1: Download Dataset
        DL->>HF: GET dataset<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: HF_TOKEN (optional)
        HF-->>DL: Dataset files
        DL->>S3: GET dataset (alternative)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
        S3-->>DL: Dataset files
        DL->>PVC: Write to /data

        Argo->>Train: Step 2: Submit Training Job
        Train->>K8s: POST TrainingJob CR<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8s->>TrainerPods: Schedule GPU worker pods
        TrainerPods->>PVC: Read dataset, write checkpoints
        TrainerPods-->>Train: Stream logs + completion status

        Argo->>Eval: Step 3: Evaluate Model
        Eval->>PVC: Load trained model
        Eval->>vLLM: Local GPU inference
        vLLM-->>Eval: Benchmark results (MMLU, GSM8K, etc.)

        Argo->>Deploy: Step 4: Register Model
        Deploy->>ModelReg: POST model metadata<br/>HTTP/8080, plaintext<br/>Auth: None
        ModelReg-->>Deploy: Model version ID
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 3: AutoRAG Optimization Pipeline
        User->>KFP: Submit AutoRAG pipeline run
        KFP->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow

        Note right of Argo: Steps: test_data_loader →<br/>documents_discovery →<br/>text_extraction →<br/>search_space_preparation →<br/>rag_templates_optimization →<br/>leaderboard_evaluation

        Argo->>S3: Load test data + discover documents<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
        S3-->>Argo: JSON test data + document list
        Argo->>S3: Download documents for extraction<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
        S3-->>Argo: Document files (PDF, DOCX, etc.)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 4: AutoML Tabular Training Pipeline
        User->>KFP: Submit AutoML pipeline run
        KFP->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow

        Note right of Argo: Steps: automl_data_loader →<br/>autogluon_models_training →<br/>leaderboard_evaluation

        Argo->>S3: Stream CSV data<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
        S3-->>Argo: CSV dataset
        Argo->>PVC: Write train/test splits
        Note right of Argo: AutoGluon training<br/>(local computation)
        Argo->>PVC: Write model metrics
    end
